The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Twain had a population of 75. The population density was {{convert|10.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Twain was 64 (85%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 5 (7%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (1%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 3 (4%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 2 (3%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 4 persons (5%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Twain CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0680952 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

There were 32 households, out of which 5 (16%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 9 (28%) were married-couple households, 6 (19%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 6 (19%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 11 (34%) had a male householder with no partner present. 12 households (38%) were one person, and 10 (31%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.34.<ref name=DP1/> There were 14 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (44% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Twain CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0680952 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 10 people (13%) under the age of 18, 4 people (5%) aged 18 to 24, 8 people (11%) aged 25 to 44, 21 people (28%) aged 45 to 64, and 32 people (43%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 62.2{{nbsp}}years. There were 31 males and 44 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 43 housing units at an average density of {{convert|6.0|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 32 (74%) were occupied. Of these, 12 were owner-occupied and 20 were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

At the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]], the median household income was $16,071 and the median family income  was $10,313. The per capita income for the CDP was $19,472. There were 70.6% of families and 72.1% of the population living below the [[poverty line]], including no under eighteens and 100.0% of those over 64.<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref>

